  "detailedRequirements": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">Welcome to the architectural validation challenge for the Social Jukebox project, the sister challenge to our </span><u style=\"text-decoration:none\"><a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/challenge-details/30051375/?type=design&amp;noncache=true\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">current design work.</a></u></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>[Social Jukebox, </strong><em>descriptive noun</em><strong>:</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\"> An autonomous Jukebox that automatically adapts the playlist based on the audience&rsquo;s preferences</span><strong>]</strong></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">We&rsquo;re excited to bring your expert opinions into the design process for this application! We&rsquo;re looking to build a user friendly app that sits on mobile and tablet devices and enables &ldquo;zones&rdquo; in a room (based on bluetooth beacon(s) or geofenced areas) to have playlists generated automatically based on the musical preferences of the people in those areas.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">To do this the mobile device will sync information with the Jukebox service based on your most recently played songs, priority of play frequency and the date the songs were last played. You, the user, will check in or out of a zone which will trigger re-generation of the playlist based on all of the currently checked in user&rsquo;s preferences.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">The ambience of areas around the Social Jukeboxes will thus be generated and tailored to users within the zones!</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">The expected deliverable for this challenge is a detailed analysis of our proposed solution and suggestions to improve or include varying other components for the technology stack as well as proposing other potential paths forward. Justifying choices and clearing explaining why you agree with various pieces, and why you would diverge from our proposed solution is very important.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><em>Judging will be entirely subjective and will be based on the interpretation of multiple members of the challenge architect team within Appirio.</em></span></p>\n",
  "digitalRunPoints": null,
  "directUrl": "https://www.topcoder.com/direct/contest/detail.action?projectId=30051381",
  "finalSubmissionGuidelines": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">You can download the images representing each diagram described below in the challenge forum. Please also download the Suggestions &amp; Justifications document as a potential starting point for your thinking around this solution. First we&rsquo;ll describe the system to be implemented and then the associated diagrams.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>So How Does This Work?</strong></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">Once the app is installed on your mobile device, it scans through your most recent playlist (including Spotify if linked) and prioritizes each song based on the play frequencies and dates. The app syncs your personal preferences with the Jukebox service.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">Each time you, or any other user, checks in or out of a zone the Jukebox service will re-generate a playlist based on the preferences of all checked-in user&rsquo;s preferences (including some random element to be defined). Each zone will thus be tailored to the musical preferences of the users currently there.</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">The concept of a VIP user can also be used to give various people temporary or permanent rights to have their musical choices treated preferentially for playlist choice.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">There needs to be a simple dashboard and control panel showing which songs were played in which zones and in various time-frames (by day, week, month etc.). Creative data visualizations are encouraged to be submitted as part of your submission here (e.g. the &ldquo;mood&rdquo; of a zone based on playlists, the behaviour of zones and patterns of musical choice potentially all combined with external factors such as environment - wow look! it&rsquo;s sunny outside and suddenly everyone&rsquo;s playing britpop!)</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">We&rsquo;re looking for solutions that mash-up proven (or exciting new!) services preferentially to creating a homegrown solution. Points that should be kept in the forefront of your creative thinking include: it *must* be scalable, the service side should handle the heavy lifting, and the app should be something lightweight and easy to port across platforms and technologies.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Associated Definitions</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Mobile App</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The Social Jukebox Mobile app that represents the user and communicates their state &amp; location</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Jukebox/DJ Service</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The cloud based system for managing Users, Playlists and the overall system</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Audio Manager</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The system ingesting the music playlist and controlling the Audio System</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Audio System</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The physical hardware playing the music</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Zone</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: A physical location with it&rsquo;s own Audio System</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Playlist</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: A list of songs designated to a Zone</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Beacon</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The physical hardware within a Zone that alerts the Mobile App to the location it is present in</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>User</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The user of the mobile app of type Visitor, VIP or regular user. </span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Calendar System</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: The system of record for User visits</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Calendar Event</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">: A visit by a user at a specific date/time &amp; location(Zone)</span></span></p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Diagram Descriptions</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Basic Jukebox System Flow</span></span></p>\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">This diagram shows the basic &ldquo;jukebox&rdquo; flow. Illustrated here is what occurs when a user&rsquo;s mobile app picks up on a Beacon within a Zone. The mobile app extracts the metadata from the user&rsquo;s music library and/or music account and sends this information to the Jukebox System. The System then adds their tracks to the playlist that is designated for that Zone. VIP users get special priority on the playlist and can manipulate the listing. The Audio System is then just a puppet to the playlist that is designated for its zone, playing whatever is in the playlist at that time.</span></span></p>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Visitor System Flow</span></span></p>\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">This diagram highlights the flow from the moment a visiting User&rsquo;s app picks up a &ldquo;front desk&rdquo; beacon. The system identifies the user and queries for their existence in the Calendaring system. Upon finding the visitor&rsquo;s event details the System sends the mobile app the details about their visit and notifies the User. </span></span></p>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Once in their meeting area, any Zone Beacons there will kick off the Basic Jukebox System Flow</span></span></p>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">System Component 1: Mobile App</span></span></p>\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">This diagram simply highlights the 3 high level capabilities of the app</span></span></p>\n\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Register/Login and listen for Zone Beacons</span></span></p>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">React to a Zone Beacon and kick off the Flow</span></span></p>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Allow for VIP manipulation of the Zone Playlist</span></span></p>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">System Component 2: (two possible stacks)</span></span></p>\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">OPTION a: Jukebox/DJ Service-JAWS Build</span></span></p>\n\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">This diagram simply displays a possible &ldquo;Serverless&rdquo; stack using Amazon&rsquo;s new, event driven Lambda service. </span></span></p>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">OPTION b: Jukebox/DJ Service-MEAN Build on PaaS offering</span></span></p>\n\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li dir=\"ltr\">\n\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">This diagram simply displays a Heroku/PaaS hosted M.E.A.N. stack. The M.E.A.N. stack utilizes Mongo (datastore), Express (service routing), Angular (front end UI) and Node.js (server). </span></span></p>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px; line-height:1.6\">Thanks for reading and good luck!</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
